sentences.en: Hornbills, starlings, vultures, rollers, bee eaters and shrikes typify the ubiquitous 1 avifauna 2 of the Kruger.
sentences.cn: 犀鸟 、 椋鸟 、 秃鹫 、 金丝雀 、 蜂虎和伯劳是克鲁格常见鸟类中的典型品种.

sentences.en: In this book we have tried to typify the main classes of verbs.
sentences.cn: 在本书中,我们力图以明显的方式把动词划分几大类.

sentences.en: New singers whose voices typify different feelings sing old songs again as their own rendition.
sentences.cn: 新歌手用他们不同的嗓音唱出不同味道的歌曲.
以甘地为典型代表的非暴力抗议

sentences.en: Rather, speculation, conflicts, and theoretical extrapolation typify their every action.
sentences.cn: 相反, 怀疑 、 冲突和理论上的推断是他们每步行为的特征.

sentences.en: the features which typify a Scottish Highland landscape
sentences.cn: 苏格兰高地典型的地貌特征
这些名称反映了当地的特色.

sentences.en: These two buildings typify the rich extremes of Irish architecture.
sentences.cn: 这两座建筑物体现了爱尔兰建筑风格的极致多变。

sentences.en: These two buildings typify the rich extremes of local architecture.
sentences.cn: 这两座建筑物代表着当地建筑风格的迥异。

sentences.en: This single item will suffice to typify all the rest.
Those five pages also typify his odd priorities.
sentences.cn: 那5页也是他古怪优先权的典型例子.

sentences.en: Two recent cars typify the current state of the art with car faces.
sentences.cn: 最近的两辆车最能说明汽车前脸设计的现状.
